      <p>A distant cousin to the <a href="ch64.html#MonstersDr-Dw2">true dragons</a>, the <a href="ch72s18.html#MonstersT-Z138">wyvern</a> is a huge flying <a href="ch73s25.html#MonstersAnimals90">lizard</a> with a poisonous stinger in its tail.<a href="img/MonstersT-Z.Wyvern.jpg" target="_blank"><span class="inlinemediaobject"><img src="thumb/MonstersT-Z.Wyvern.jpg" align="right"/></span></a></p>
      <p>A <a href="ch72s18.html#MonstersT-Z138">wyvern's</a> body is 15 feet long, and dark brown to gray; half that length is tail. Its wingspan is about 20 feet. A <a href="ch72s18.html#MonstersT-Z138">wyvern</a> weighs about one ton.</p>
      <p><a href="ch72s18.html#MonstersT-Z138">Wyverns</a> speak Draconic, but usually don't bother with anything more elaborate than a loud hiss or a deep-throated growl much like that of a bull alligator.</p>
      <div class="sect4" lang="en">
        <div class="titlepage">
          <div>
            <div>
              <h5 class="title"><a name="id2243176"/>Combat</h5>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="keywordset" style="display:none">
          <div class="keyword">monsterinfo</div>
        </div>
        <a class="indexterm" name="MonstersT-Z139"/>
        <p><a href="ch72s18.html#MonstersT-Z138">Wyverns</a> are rather stupid but always aggressive: They attack nearly anything that isn't obviously more powerful than themselves. A <a href="ch72s18.html#MonstersT-Z138">wyvern</a> dives from the air, snatching the opponent with its talons and stinging it to death. A <a href="ch72s18.html#MonstersT-Z138">wyvern</a> can slash with its talons only when making a flyby attack.</p>
        <div class="simplesect" lang="en">
          <div class="titlepage"/>
          <a name="id2243228"/>
          <div class="keywordset" style="display:none">
            <div class="keyword">other</div>
          </div>
          <a class="indexterm" name="MonstersT-Z140"/>
          <p><span class="strong"><strong>Improved Grab (Ex):</strong></span> To use this ability, a <a href="ch72s18.html#MonstersT-Z138">wyvern</a> must hit with its talons. It can then attempt to start a grapple as a free action without provoking an attack of opportunity. If it wins the grapple check, it establishes a hold and stings.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="simplesect" lang="en">
          <div class="titlepage"/>
          <a name="id2243269"/>
          <div class="keywordset" style="display:none">
            <div class="keyword">other</div>
          </div>
          <a class="indexterm" name="MonstersT-Z141"/>
          <p><span class="strong"><strong>Poison (Ex):</strong></span> Injury, Fortitude DC 17, initial and secondary damage 2d6 Con. The save DC is Constitution-based.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="simplesect" lang="en">
          <div class="titlepage"/>
          <a name="id2243298"/>
          <div class="keywordset" style="display:none">
            <div class="keyword">other</div>
          </div>
          <a class="indexterm" name="MonstersT-Z142"/>
          <p><span class="strong"><strong>Skills:</strong></span> <a href="ch72s18.html#MonstersT-Z138">Wyverns</a> have a +3 racial bonus on <a href="ch16s03.html#CombinedSkills294">Spot</a> checks.</p>
